Closing Statement
As this model demonstrates, every disaster contains multiple variables already in motion.
What appears to be a single event is, in reality, a domino sequence of hazards, failures, and cascading impacts.

By mapping these chains explicitly — hazard → linker → downstream hazard — we acknowledge the true complexity of disaster behavior and create the foundation for systems that can act with clarity instead of guesswork.

It is our goal to build a system capable of saving lives during an event and reducing suffering in the aftermath by delivering real‑time, multi‑hazard awareness.
Through accurate disaster chaining, we aim to give responders, agencies, and communities the ability to see not just what has happened, but what is likely to happen next — and act before the cascade accelerates.
